⚠️ SEVERITY DISCREPANCY DETECTED — ANALYST REVIEW REQUIRED
NVD [1] scores this CVSS 9.9 CRITICAL; the CNA-published record at CVE.org [3] scores it CVSS v4.0 4.7 MEDIUM. The rule below uses T1190 and classtype:attempted-admin reflecting the higher NVD score, but the true severity is disputed. Analyst must adjudicate before promoting to production.

NOTE: CVE-2026-0284 is 3 days old [1] with exploit maturity rated UNREPORTED [2]. No confirmed public exploit payloads are available. The content matches below target generic XML injection patterns observable in LSVPN HTTP traffic and should be treated as low-fidelity heuristics pending vendor-confirmed indicators. This is a PROPOSED DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0284 PAN-OS LSVPN XML injection attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri; content:"/ssl-vpn/"; nocase;
  http.request_body;
  pcre:"/(?:<[^>]*(?:&#x[0-9a-f]+;|%3C|%3E|\x00)[^>]*>|<!\[CDATA\[|<!ENTITY\s)/i";
  threshold:type limit, track by_src, count 3, seconds 60;
  reference:cve,2026-0284;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000084; rev:1; )

